HOUSE BILL No. 1016
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
insurance.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 27-8-24.8 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]:
4 Chapter 24.8. Selection of Primary Care Provider
5 Sec. 1. This chapter applies to a policy of accident and sickness
6 insurance that is issued, delivered, amended, or renewed after June
7 30, 2026.
8 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "insured" means an individual
9 entitled to coverage under a policy of accident and sickness
10 insurance.
11 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "policy of accident and sickness
12 insurance" has the meaning set forth in IC 27-8-5-1. The term does
13 not include a policy, plan, or coverage set forth in IC 27-8-5-2.5(a).
14 Sec. 4. Subject to section 7 of this chapter, a policy of accident
15 and sickness insurance that requires an insured to select a primary
16 care provider to receive coverage may permit an insured to select
17 a participating provider who is:
2026 IN 1016—LS 6213/DI 141

2
1 (1) a physical therapist to provide physical therapy services;
2 or
3 (2) an occupational therapist to provide occupational therapy
4 services.
5 Sec. 5. A policy of accident and sickness insurance must clearly
6 state in literature explaining the policy the options available to an
7 insured under section 4 of this chapter.
8 Sec. 6. A policy of accident and sickness insurance may not
9 impose a higher premium, a higher copayment requirement, or any
10 other additional expense on an insured because the insured selected
11 a primary care provider in accordance with this chapter.
12 Sec. 7. Nothing in this chapter permits:
13 (1) a physical therapist to practice physical therapy outside of
14 the physical therapist's scope of practice under IC 25-27; or
15 (2) an occupational therapist to practice occupational therapy
16 outside of the occupational therapist's scope of practice under
17 IC 25-23.5.
18 SECTION 2. IC 27-13-37-1.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
19 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
20 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1.5. (a) This section applies to an
21 individual contract and a group contract that is entered into,
22 delivered, amended, or renewed after June 30, 2026.
23 (b) Subject to subsection (e), a health maintenance organization
24 that requires an enrollee to select a primary care provider to
25 receive coverage may permit an enrollee to select a participating
26 provider who is:
27 (1) a physical therapist to provide physical therapy services;
28 or
29 (2) an occupational therapist to provide occupational therapy
30 services.
31 (c) An individual contract or a group contract must clearly state
32 in literature explaining the contract the options available to an
33 enrollee under subsection (b).
34 (d) A health maintenance organization may not impose a higher
35 premium, a higher copayment requirement, or any other
36 additional expense on an enrollee because the enrollee selected a
37 primary care provider in accordance with this section.
38 (e) Nothing in this section permits:
39 (1) a physical therapist to practice physical therapy outside of
40 the physical therapist's scope of practice under IC 25-27; or
41 (2) an occupational therapist to practice occupational therapy
42 outside of the occupational therapist's scope of practice under
